text: in short, while it’s not a blatantly *wrong* decision, it could have been handled better. (5/5)

author: Sehr Dada
text:
if nikita mazepin were to speak up about the situation, his seat could have been decided based on moral judgement — a fairer approach.

what we also can’t ignore is how ukrali sponsorship would affect his seat & their involvement with mazepin able to have a drive in F1. (4/5)

author: Sehr Dada
text:
F1 and FIA have made themselves clear on two “political opinions”.
1) via their statement and by discontinuing the sochi gp they condemn russian actions
2) their 2022 regulations explicitly encourage social & political *action*
(3/5)

author: Sehr Dada
text: speaking out about a literal invasion that’s causes numerous deaths, casualties and is even referred to as WW3 is not a mere “political opinion”. more than that, it’s an important opinion that speaks to his values and thought process (2/5)

author: Sehr Dada
text:
a hot take no one asked for:

to ban mazepin based on solely where he’s born is wrong. But dmitry mazepin, his father, maintains strong ties to putin and endorses the invasion of ukraine. the bare minimum required to keep his seat would be to speak out about the situation. (1/5)
